<rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Theatre</rs>: stage area</rs>
<rs type="origLocation"><rs type="monuList">Theatre</rs> proskeneion frieze. at north end. Inscribed on the blocks which make up the cornice, of the Doric order, above <xref type="iAph">536</xref>,  the inscription of Zoilos, across the back of the Theatre stage. The blocks have simple moulding above, supporting water spouts in the form of lions' heads; the underside has a decoration of mutules. </rs>
<rs type="lastLocation">Findspot, restored at north end.</rs>
</p>
